  "prompt": "What are Hazel eyes?",
  "response": "Hazel eyes are a type of eye color that is characterized by a combination of brown and green pigmentation, often with flecks of gold or yellow. The color can appear to change depending on the lighting conditions and the colors of clothing or makeup worn by the person. Hazel eyes are relatively rare, occurring in about 5-8% of the world's population. They are most common in people of European descent, but can be found in people of many different ethnic backgrounds.",
